FEV

Week 10

1 FEV

FEV (forced expiratory volume) is an index of pulmonary function that measures the volume of air expelled after one second of constant effort.

The data contains

  • \(n=654\) children
  • aged 6-22
  • from Childhood Respiratory Disease Study (1980 Boston, Massachusetts)
  • two of the predictor variables recorded were Smoking Status and Age

2 Read in data

fev <- read_csv(here::here("data", "fev.csv"))

4 Clean data

fev <- 
  fev %>% 
  mutate(
    log_fev = log(FEV)
  )
